Preheat the oven to 150C/130C Fan/Gas 2.Tip the anchovies and garlic onto a board. Using the back of a knife, crush the two together to form a rough paste.In an ovenproof baking dish layer the vegetables â€“ parsnips, potatoes, white onion and then a little of the anchovy and garlic paste. Repeat the layers until done. Pour over the cream.Bake for 45 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender and the top is golden-brown.